Description: An ODE-based box model for simulating indoor air chemistry,
    including gas-phase photochemistry (SAPRC99 and SAPRC07T mechanisms),
    ventilation, surface deposition, indoor emissions from occupant
    activities, and natural and artificial lighting. Integrates the TUV
    (Tropospheric Ultraviolet and Visible) radiation model to calculate
    indoor photolysis rates from outdoor solar conditions and building
    optical properties. Optional analyses include time derivatives, mass
    balance component separation, first-order sensitivity analysis, and
    uncertainty propagation. Two usage modes are provided: (1) an
    interactive Shiny GUI launched via runSIACSApp(), with both a
    step-by-step Wizard and a full Advanced interface; (2) a batch mode
    via SIACS.batch() for programmatic, parallelised multi-scenario runs.
